    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-arrabbiata-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Peel and slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-arrabbiata-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and your <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant \u2013 this is your <strong>chilli oil</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-arrabbiata-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Trim the ends off your<strong> Tenderstem broccoli</strong> then chop into thirds</p><p>Grate your <strong>Italian hard cheese</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-arrabbiata-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato & mozzarella tortelloni </strong>and <strong>chopped Tenderstem broccoli </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>tortelloni</strong> and <strong>broccoli</strong>, reserving a cup of the<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-arrabbiata-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the tortelloni is cooking, add your <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, <strong>tomato paste</strong>, and <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>to the pan with the chilli oil</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>sugar</strong> and a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and cook for 2-3 min or until thickened</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-arrabbiata-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once thickened, add the <strong>drained tortelloni</strong> and<strong> broccoli </strong>to the pan, tear in <strong>half</strong> your <strong>basil </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) and give everything a gentle mix up until the pasta is coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your<strong> spicy arrabbiata sauce with tomato & mozzarella tortelloni</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-arrabbiata-with-tomato-and-mozzarella-tortelloni/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spicy arrabbiata sauce with tomato & mozzarella tortelloni </strong>topped with your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>Tear over the <strong>remaining basil</strong></p><p>Season with a grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>and drizzle everything with a little <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
